description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Medicine &amp; Emergency Care Division for bank zero hours ward receptionists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts are particularly attractive as they supports a wide range of reception duties, ranging from face to face reception cover to arranging transport, patient notes and whiteboard management. The hours will be as and when required. Our receptionists working hours are 0800-1600 Monday to Friday&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main emphasis of the roles are to provide a comprehensive reception service to the wards within the General Medicine Care Unit, whilst working in conjunction with a multidisciplinary team and liaising with internal and external stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties will include front of house, face to face receptionist service to all patients and visitors, maintaining patient notes and the Open ward / Medway system, filing, and producing documents to a high standard, ensuring that accuracy and confidentiality is maintained.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful in this role you will possess excellent interpersonal and IT skills, to include GCSE Maths and English grade A–C (or equivalent) and have relevant office/secretarial experience. You must have effective communication skills and be adaptable to meet the service needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of medical terminology, customer care and previous NHS experience are also desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
